         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">3/2/87 ¶  ¶ A letter has just reached me, dear Dr Ramsay, from the greatest living Algologist, Prof. Agardh, ¶  in which he expresses his full concurrence with my views, that the Claudea Bennettiana m...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.02.03</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Ramsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.562, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">3/2/87</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A letter has just reached me, dear Dr Ramsay, from the greatest living Algologist, Prof. Agardh,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See J. Agardh to M, 25 December 1886 (in this edition as 86-12-25b).</p>
               </note> in which he expresses his full concurrence with my views, that the <name key="Claudea%20Bennettiana">Claudea Bennettiana</name> must be transferred to an other genus, and that it is nearer Vanvorstia</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>But it may be, as he admits, the type of a new genus, should the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fruits</hi>
               </seg> exhibit any particular peculiarities. Now, as you have discovered a new locality for this beautiful and rare plant, it would be well, if you could kindly follow up your discovery, so that also the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fruit</hi>
               </seg> may be obtained and the other organs of propagation or generation. Of course you will get every acknowledgement.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Claudea%20Bennettiana">Claudea Bennettiana</name>
            </p>
         </div>
